The paper deals with the construction of finite automata for recognizing subsequences of a given string, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the size and delay of the automata, which are related to topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents a novel hierarchical automata construction, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
